SP  - 121
EP  - 129
VL  - 4
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article is a response to a critique of behavior modification theory applied to organizations that was made by Edwin A. Locke. The issues in contention include: the deterministic viewpoint to explain human behavior; lack of a scientific base for behavior modification theory; inconsistency of vicarious learning with behavior-modification principles; the idea that behavior modification cannot work unless people are aware of and managers have control over contingencies; and the role of punishment in behavior modification.
